Senate Resolution 255
By: Senators Summers of the 13th, Robertson of the 29th, Gooch of the 51st, Kennedy of the
18th, Walker III of the 20th and others
ADOPTED SENATE
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Senate Study Committee on Combating Unscrupulous Companion Animal
2 Breeding Practices; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, unscrupulous companion animal breeding may include puppy mills in
4 commercial breeding facilities and backyard breeding operations; and
5 WHEREAS, unscrupulous companion animal breeding is the practice of breeding animals
6 for financial gain without regard for the animal's health or well-being; and
7 WHEREAS, unscrupulous companion animal breeding negatively impacts taxpayers who
8 often bear the burden of cleanup costs when breeding operations are busted and causes
9 financial strain on existing animal shelters and rescue organizations; and
10 WHEREAS, stray and feral animal populations can pose a public safety threat to humans
11 with increases in dog bites or attacks, pack behavior in stray dogs, and damage to property
12 and livestock, and they are more likely to be involved in traffic accidents; and
