13 WHEREAS, unscrupulous companion animal breeding contributes to an increase in unowned
14 and stray animals and can lead to disease and infection outbreaks among stray and feral
15 animal populations and poses a threat to local ecosystems; and
16 WHEREAS, despite state and local laws regulating animal breeding, enforcement remains
17 inconsistent and additional education and research on best practices are needed; and
18 WHEREAS, unscrupulous companion animal breeders may not comply with appropriate
19 licensing or permitting requirements; and
20 WHEREAS, companion animals raised by these breeders often suffer from inhumane living
21 conditions, physical and mental health conditions, and lack of socialization and are often
22 victims of illegal puppy trading; and
23 WHEREAS, companion animals raised by these breeders are more likely to experience
24 animal suffering and euthanasia; and
25 WHEREAS, unscrupulous companion animal breeding can foster behavioral problems in
26 companion animals, which can lead to companion animal abandonment and abuse; and
27 WHEREAS, unscrupulous companion animal breeding can negatively impact neighborhood
28 communities and often burden local authorities; and
29 WHEREAS, a study committee is needed to establish informed recommendations on
30 reducing or preventing unscrupulous companion animal breeding to ensure humane treatment
31 of animals in breeding practices in this state.
